modules.description: This module implements an in-memory file system with operations for creating, reading, writing, and managing files and directories. It supports data types like `Cstruct.t` for binary data and `string` paths, along with standard result types for error handling. Concrete use cases include simulating file system behavior in test environments and building lightweight, ephemeral storage layers for applications.

This module provides an in-memory filesystem implementation supporting file and directory operations using string paths and page-aligned buffers (`Cstruct.t`). It includes error types for handling failures in read, write, and file management operations, enabling robust in-memory file simulation. The module supports creating, reading, writing, and traversing files and directories, making it suitable for testing filesystem logic without disk I/O or building transient storage layers. Submodules extend this functionality with additional structures and utilities for managing in-memory file hierarchies and data manipulation.
